The most common complication of subarachnoid hemorrhage is arterial vasospasm. Blindness can occur in some cases, but it is not the most common complication. Hemorrhagic shock is not a complication of subarachnoid hemorrhage. Bacterial meningitis is a separate condition and not associated with subarachnoid hemorrhage.
